statement:
To find a point (\emph{a},\emph{cos(a)}) on the graph of \emph{y =
cos(x)} whose tangent line goes through the origin, which of the
following equations must you solve?

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  \textbf{(a)} $\cot(a)= a$
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  \textbf{(b)} $\cot(a)= -a$
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  \textbf{(c)} $\tan(a)= a$
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  \textbf{(d)} $\tan(a)= -a$
\end{itemize}
